										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<h2 id="why-i-need-the-bulk-delete-option">Why I need the Bulk Delete option?</h2>



<p>A few months back I launched a WordPress Website and today when I visited it I saw that my blog has 10,326 Comments. I knew the moment when I saw it that this is all spam. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="218" height="40" src="https://iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/image.png" alt="" class="wp-image-772"/></figure>



<h2 id="why-the-existing-bulk-delete-option-in-wordpress-sucks-alternate-solution">Why the existing Bulk Delete option in WordPress Sucks? Alternate solution.</h2>



<p>The primary reason for any Bulk Actions + Checkbox like the ones which I show in the image below image selects only the items on the page itself. Which are like 20 items out of over 500 pages. (Remember I have 10,326 Comments) </p>



<span id="more-771"></span>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="861" height="591" src="https://iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/image-1.png" alt="" class="wp-image-773" srcset="https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095532/image-1.png 861w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095532/image-1-300x206.png 300w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095532/image-1-768x527.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 861px) 100vw, 861px" /></figure>



<p>Alternatively, if it worked like how the Bulk Action items work in Gmail. I wouldn&#8217;t have to write this mail. </p>



<p>See in the screenshot below, how Gmail gives me an option to select all between 50 conversation on the page and all the 9065 conversations when I use the Checkbox to select all the Items. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image alignfull size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="1024" height="142" src="https://iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/image-2-1024x142.png" alt="" class="wp-image-774" srcset="https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095533/image-2-1024x142.png 1024w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095533/image-2-300x42.png 300w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095533/image-2-768x106.png 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095533/image-2.png 1530w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>It would have been so much great if the WordPress also had a similar option to allow me to select all 10,326. But unfortunately it&#8217;s not there as of 5.6.2 Versioni of WordPress it is not there. </p>



<h2 id="how-i-fixed-the-problem">How I fixed the problem?</h2>



<p>Well Google is always there for my Rescue. And I found a Plugin that can help me in deleting all the Comments at once. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/delete-all-comments-of-website/"><img loading="lazy" width="745" height="147" src="https://iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/image-3.png" alt="Delete all WordPress comments Plugin" class="wp-image-775" srcset="https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095534/image-3.png 745w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095534/image-3-300x59.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /></a></figure>



<p>This is the first thing that pops up when. <br>When I searched for it in the plugins section it said it has not been tested with the current version of WordPress. But since my blog does not have almost anything. I can go ahead. </p>



<p>After installation and Activation of the plugin you can find the menu to delete under </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="263" height="352" src="https://iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/image-4.png" alt="Delete Comments in Menu. " class="wp-image-776" srcset="https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095535/image-4.png 263w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095535/image-4-224x300.png 224w" sizes="(max-width: 263px) 100vw, 263px" /></figure>



<p>These are the options that the Delete Plugin gives. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image alignfull size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="1024" height="445" src="https://iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/image-5-1024x445.png" alt="Available options for Delete Comments Plugin. " class="wp-image-777" srcset="https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095535/image-5-1024x445.png 1024w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095535/image-5-300x130.png 300w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095535/image-5-768x334.png 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095535/image-5-1536x668.png 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095535/image-5.png 1692w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>Well for my purpose, I wanted to delete all the comments from A-Z so I do not need any complex options. But you might, so you can search for some other plugin if this does not have what you need. </p>



<p>I just selected the and pressed &#8220;Delete Now Button&#8221; and Comments and got the following popup. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="663" height="447" src="https://iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/image-6.png" alt="Success Message after all the comments have been deleted by the wordpress Delete All comments plugin. 
" class="wp-image-778" srcset="https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095537/image-6.png 663w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/live.iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/03095537/image-6-300x202.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 663px) 100vw, 663px" /></figure>



<p>Well, but to see the Comments Count in the menu bar disappear, I had to just refresh the Page. </p>



<p>Anyways, this time I did not &#8220;Buy a Beer&#8221; to the developer Navneet Soni. But it really did save me a a lot of time. A big thanks goes to him. </p>



<h2 id="steps-you-can-follow">Steps you can follow. </h2>



<div class="schema-how-to wp-block-yoast-how-to-block"><p class="schema-how-to-description">How to Delete all the comments from your WordPress. </p> <ol class="schema-how-to-steps"><li class="schema-how-to-step" id="how-to-step-1614190245466"><strong class="schema-how-to-step-name">Login into your WordPress and Navigate to Add New Plugin</strong> <p class="schema-how-to-step-text"><img alt="" src="https://iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/add_new_plugin.png"/></p> </li><li class="schema-how-to-step" id="how-to-step-1614190397511"><strong class="schema-how-to-step-name">In the Keyword Box enter &#8220;Delete All comments&#8221;</strong> <p class="schema-how-to-step-text"><img alt="" src="https://iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/delete_allcomments.png"/></p> </li><li class="schema-how-to-step" id="how-to-step-1614190614899"><strong class="schema-how-to-step-name">Select the Plugin by Navneet Soni and hit &#8220;Install Now&#8221; button. <br/>Note the plugin has 20000+ Active Installation with 5 <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/2b50.png" alt="⭐" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/2b50.png" alt="⭐" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/2b50.png" alt="⭐" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/2b50.png" alt="⭐" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/2b50.png" alt="⭐" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" />(Wow)</strong> <p class="schema-how-to-step-text"><img alt="" src="https://iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/plugin_image.png"/></p> </li><li class="schema-how-to-step" id="how-to-step-1614190658597"><strong class="schema-how-to-step-name">Once the Installation is done the button will change to &#8220;Activate&#8221;, then press the &#8220;Activate&#8221; button. <br/></strong> <p class="schema-how-to-step-text"><img alt="" src="https://iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/activate.png"/></p> </li><li class="schema-how-to-step" id="how-to-step-1614190979613"><strong class="schema-how-to-step-name">Select your Preferred delete option and hit Delete. <br/> </strong> <p class="schema-how-to-step-text"><img alt="" src="https://iamshishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/delete_opt.png"/></p> </li><li class="schema-how-to-step" id="how-to-step-1614191214334"><strong class="schema-how-to-step-name">Deactivate and remove the plugin. <br/>Well this is an optional step, but I prefer to keep by wordpress light. So if i know I no longer require the plugin, I deactivate and delete the plugin. <br/>So you too can chose to do so. </strong> <p class="schema-how-to-step-text"></p> </li></ol></div>



<p>Well, If you have any further Ideas on how to delete the comments, that is faster and better than this plugin. Please share with me in the comments. </p>



<p></p>
